      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "pipeline: normalized provider→channel stream grammar (core)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nNormalizes every provider wire format into **one** event grammar — final text, thinking/reasoning, narration/commentary, tool activity, usage, errors — under **emit always, archive always, gate only at presentation**. This is the **core half** of a stacked pair; the Discord presentation gate follows on top (see below).\n\nDesign narrative + full normative spec, evidence captures, and a 35-test conformance harness:\n- RFC: openclaw/rfcs#16 — https://github.com/openclaw/rfcs/pull/16\n- Spec repo: https://github.com/Marvinthebored/openclaw-provider-stream-spec\n\nExtends the agent event I/O contract (`docs/channels/agent-event-io-contract.md`, #92216); four points are marked **[AMENDS BASE]** in the spec.\n\n## What's in this PR (core only)\n\n- Adapters **emit always**: wire-carried reasoning is no longer dropped at the source (`streamReasoning && onReasoningStream` gate and the `emitReasoning` discard removed as *emission* gates; `onReasoningStream` survives as a channel render hook).\n- Normalized `thinking` (raw/summary/redacted, dual-lane dedup), `assistant` commentary/final phases, tool `start`-at-earliest, lifecycle terminal + synthetic `stream_closed`.\n- Finality resolution: durable final **replaces** the draft segment (no dedup heuristics); zero-text finalize emits no final; Reject is a destructive settle.\n- Dispatch gates reasoning/narration at presentation; gateway mirrors thinking on its own stream + archives the normalized sequence.\n- **deepseek reasoning/text boundary sealed** — the reasoning stream closes when text begins without a `thinking_end` signal, so the final no longer folds into the thinking block.\n- **Snapshot-commentary dedupe by item id** — prevents the commentary flood under emit-always; the fix is in core, so it protects every channel (this absorbs the former stacked flood PR).\n- Catalog: kimi-k2.6/k2.5 marked as reasoning models.\n\n## Scope / stacking\n\n- **Core, dispatch, catalog only.** No channel rendering here.\n- Discord presentation gate is stacked on this branch: `Marvinthebored:pipeline-discord` (Marvinthebored/openclaw#2; its isolated diff is Discord-only). It requires this PR to run.\n- Each branch is independently checkout-able so contributors can patch and test ahead of landing.\n\n## Status / testing\n\n- **Rebased onto `v2026.6.9`** (was a ~2-day-old merge-base). The earlier \"behind main / overlapping files\" caveat is resolved; conflicts in the Discord-lane + streaming hot area were reconciled against current upstream.\n- Several constituent fixes from this effort have since **landed upstream independently** and are in 6.9 (e.g. #93343 codex commentary-dedup, #93124 telegram progress previews); the contract base #92216 is merged.\n- `tsgo:core` ✓ / `tsgo:extensions` ✓ / full build ✓ on the rebased tree.\n- Per-commit history preserved on the integration branch; squashed for the draft.\n\n## Resolved since the first draft\n\n- **deepseek reasoning/text boundary** — fixed (see above).\n- **#92216 sequencing** — unblocked (#92216 merged 2026-06-13).\n\n## Remaining\n\n- Land the four `[AMENDS BASE]` points in `agent-event-io-contract.md` (now a clean follow-up; sequencing blocker #92216 is merged).\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
        "branch": "pipeline-core",
